<div class="container">

     <header class="header">
        <h1>Report Management in Movelys</h1>
    </header>

    <!-- Introduction Section -->
    <section class="introduction">
        <h2>Introduction</h2>
        <p>
            In a business environment where data drives strategic decisions, 
            <strong>report management becomes a fundamental lever for steering and performance.</strong> 
            Movelys' reporting module is designed to give businesses a clear, detailed, and real-time 
            view of all their commercial, financial, and logistical operations.
        </p>
        <p>
            With a rich and user-friendly interface, this module automatically generates a wide variety 
            of essential reports: sales, purchases, payments, inventory, user activity, expenses, 
            profitability, customer/supplier tracking, product performance, stock transfers, and more. 
            Each report can be filtered by period, location, user, or category for targeted and relevant analysis.
        </p>
        <p>
            Movelys transforms raw data into readable and actionable insights, offering exports (PDF, Excel, CSV), 
            summary tables, charts, and performance indicators. This module enhances transparency, traceability, 
            and <strong>decision-making while adapting to each company's specific needs.</strong>
        </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 1: Profit and Loss Report -->
    <section class="section-1">
        <h2>1) Profit and Loss Report</h2>

        <article class="subsection">
            <h3>1.1) Purpose of this Interface</h3>
            <p>
                The Profit and Loss Report interface provides a detailed analysis of a company's profitability 
                over a given period. It combines accounting and operational data needed to:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Measure the cost of goods sold</li>
                <li>Calculate net profit</li>
                <li>Evaluate performance by product, customer, category, brand, date, etc.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                This report is essential for strategic decisions, financial planning, and 
                <strong>managerial accounting.</strong>
            </p>
        </article>

        <article class="subsection">
            <h3>1.2) Interface Structure</h3>
            <p>
                The interface consists of four functional blocks:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Selection filters (location, date)</strong></li>
                <li><strong>Financial report summary (left and right)</strong></li>
                <li><strong>Automatic COGS and profit calculations</strong></li>
                <li><strong>Profit breakdown by segment (bottom table)</strong></li>
            </ul>

            <h4>1.2.1) Selection Filters</h4>
            <p>
                <strong>Location selector:</strong><br>
                Filters the report by site (warehouse, store, etc.)<br>
                <strong>Date filter:</strong><br>
                Opens a calendar to define a specific analysis period
            </p>

            <h4>1.2.2) Financial Report Summary</h4>
            <p>
                This section is divided into two main columns:
            </p>
            <h5>➢ Left: Stock & Purchase Cost Data</h5>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Opening stock (purchase):</strong> Value of available stock at the start of the period, at purchase price</li>
                <li><strong>Opening stock (sale):</strong> Same, but at selling prices</li>
                <li><strong>Total purchases:</strong> Cumulative amount of purchased products</li>
                <li><strong>Total stock adjustment:</strong> Value of manual adjustments or losses</li>
                <li><strong>Total purchase shipping costs:</strong> Transport costs related to supplies</li>
                <li><strong>Additional purchase expenses:</strong> Other purchase-related charges (e.g., customs, handling)</li>
                <li><strong>Transfer shipping costs:</strong> Internal transfer expenses between sites</li>
                <li><strong>Total purchase discount:</strong> Discounts negotiated with suppliers</li>
                <li><strong>Customer reward (on sale):</strong> Discounts or bonuses granted to customers</li>
                <li><strong>Total sale return:</strong> Percentage or value of sales gain</li>
            </ul>

            <h5>➢ Right: Sales, Returns, Closing Stock</h5>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Closing stock (purchase):</strong> Value of remaining stock at the end, at purchase price</li>
                <li><strong>Closing stock (sale):</strong> Value of remaining stock at the end, at selling price</li>
                <li><strong>Total sales (excl. tax):</strong> Cumulative amount of sales made, excluding taxes</li>
                <li><strong>Shipping costs (sale):</strong> Charges incurred on sales logistics</li>
                <li><strong>Additional sale expenses:</strong> E.g., commissions, packaging, customer service</li>
                <li><strong>Recovered stock:</strong> Items returned by customers</li>
                <li><strong>Total purchase return:</strong> Goods returned to suppliers</li>
                <li><strong>Purchase discount:</strong> Discounts applied to purchases</li>
                <li><strong>Sale rounding:</strong> Rounded differences on tax-inclusive sale amounts</li>
            </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="subsection">
            <h3>1.3) Automatic Calculations – Financial Results</h3>
            <table class="component-table">
                <tr>
                    <th>Element</th>
                    <th>Meaning</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>COGS (Cost of Goods Sold)</td>
                    <td>Cost of goods sold = opening stock + purchases – closing stock</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Gross profit</td>
                    <td>Total sales – COGS</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Net profit</td>
                    <td>Gross profit – fees & discounts</td>
                </tr>
            </table>
            <p>
                These figures reflect the overall financial health of the business during the selected period.
            </p>
        </article>

        <article class="subsection">
            <h3>1.4) Profit Breakdown by Segment</h3>
            <h4>+ Segmentation Tabs</h4>
            <p>
                Users can view profits:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>By product</strong></li>
                <li><strong>By invoice</strong></li>
                <li><strong>By location</strong></li>
                <li><strong>By date</strong></li>
                <li><strong>By customer</strong></li>
                <li><strong>By category</strong></li>
                <li><strong>By brand</strong></li>
                <li><strong>By service staff</strong></li>
                <li><strong>By day</strong></li>
            </ul>

            <h5>Example of a Results Table for Products</h5>
            <table class="component-table">
                <tr>
                    <th>Column</th>
                    <th>Description</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Product</td>
                    <td>Name of the sold product</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Gross margin</td>
                    <td>Profit generated by this product (sale – cost)</td>
                </tr>
            </table>

            <p><strong>Example display:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Astral24: 80,000 FCFA margin</strong></li>
                <li><strong>Women's perfume 30%: 82,500 FCFA</strong></li>
                <li><strong>Essence perfume 100 ml: 4,500 FCFA</strong></li>
                <li><strong>Gross total: 167,000 FCFA</strong></li>
            </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="subsection">
            <h3>Associated Functions:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>✓ <strong>CSV / Excel / PDF Export:</strong> Generates user reports in the desired format.</li>
                <li>✓ <strong>Direct printing:</strong> A print button is available to produce a paper version of the list.</li>
                <li>✓ <strong>Column visibility:</strong> Allows hiding or displaying certain columns based on preferences.</li>
                <li>✓ <strong>Dynamic search:</strong> A quick search field helps locate specific users.</li>
                <li>✓ <strong>Pagination & entries per page:</strong> Users can navigate between pages and choose how many records to display per page (e.g., 10, 25, 50).</li>
            </ul>
